# Regression checklist (required)

Before merging changes under the globs above:

1. Read [REGRESSION_RISK_AUDIT_2026-05.md](../../docs/audits/REGRESSION_RISK_AUDIT_2026-05.md)
2. List verified REG-ids in the PR (e.g. `REG-001, REG-004`)
3. Run `npm test` from `baserow-app/`

## Quick rules

- **REG-001:** Bulk action bar only when 2+ checkbox-selected rows in core data (`BULK_ACTION_MIN_SELECTED_COUNT`)
- **REG-003:** Do not call bulk `handleRowSelect` from row background click — checkbox column only
- **REG-004:** Content overlays use `md:left-sidebar` on desktop so sidebar stays clickable
- **MH-RECORD-DRAWERS:** Custom block record drawers must satisfy `.cursor/rules/custom-block-record-drawers.mdc` and pass `npm test -- --run custom-block-record-drawer-regression`

## Custom block record drawer regressions

- Social Calendar item opens `social_post` layout
- Event Calendar item opens `event` layout
- Things To Do item opens `task` layout
- Campaigns Overview row opens `campaign` layout
- Content Timeline item opens `content` layout
- Resource Hub primary click opens file URL
- Resource Hub Manage asset opens `asset` layout
- Generic Grid/List/Calendar record opens generic drawer
- View/Edit does not stack drawers
- More fields contains unmatched fields
- Comments/activity still render
- Unsaved draft warning still appears
- Drawer uses `md:left-sidebar`
- In page edit mode, item click selects block instead of opening drawer

## Manual QA (custom record drawers)

- Open Social Calendar, click a social post, and verify social drawer opens
- Click Edit in social drawer and verify edit is in the same drawer (no second panel)
- Open Event Calendar, click an event, and verify event drawer opens
- Click Edit in event drawer and verify edit is in the same drawer
- Open Things To Do and verify task click opens task drawer
- Open Campaigns Overview and verify row click opens campaign drawer
- Open Content Timeline and verify item click opens content drawer
- In Resource Hub, verify primary asset click opens file URL/preview
- In Resource Hub, verify Manage asset opens asset drawer
- In Grid/List/Calendar, verify record opens generic drawer behavior
- Confirm comments/activity, draft warning, save, and delete still work
